methods.name: scan

tags.name: experimental
tags.text: This method is experimental and may change in the future.

methods.docs:
Scan a barcode with a ready-to-use interface without WebView customization.

On **Android**, this method is only available on devices with Google Play Services
installed. Therefore, no camera permission is required.

**Attention:** Before using this method on *Android*, first check if the Google Barcode Scanner module is available
by using `isGoogleBarcodeScannerModuleAvailable()`.

Only available on Android and iOS.

methods.name: isSupported
methods.docs: Returns whether or not the barcode scanner is supported.

methods.name: enableTorch
methods.docs:
Enable camera's torch (flash) during a scan session.

Only available on Android and iOS.

methods.name: disableTorch
methods.docs:
Disable camera's torch (flash) during a scan session.

Only available on Android and iOS.

methods.name: toggleTorch
methods.docs:
Toggle camera's torch (flash) during a scan session.

Only available on Android and iOS.

methods.name: isTorchEnabled
methods.docs:
Returns whether or not the camera's torch (flash) is enabled.

Only available on Android and iOS.

methods.name: isTorchAvailable
methods.docs:
Returns whether or not the camera's torch (flash) is available.

Only available on Android and iOS.

methods.name: setZoomRatio

methods.name: getMinZoomRatio

Get the maximum zoom ratio of the camera.

methods.name: openSettings
methods.docs:
Open the settings of the app so that the user can grant the camera permission.

methods.name: isGoogleBarcodeScannerModuleAvailable
methods.docs:
Check if the Google Barcode Scanner module is available.

If the Google Barcode Scanner module is not available, you can install it by using `installGoogleBarcodeScannerModule()`.

Only available on Android.

methods.name: installGoogleBarcodeScannerModule
methods.docs:
Install the Google Barcode Scanner module.

**Attention**: This only starts the installation.
The `googleBarcodeScannerModuleInstallProgress` event listener will
notify you when the installation is complete.

Only available on Android.

properties.name: formats
properties.docs:
Improve the speed of the barcode scanner by configuring
the barcode formats to scan for.

Only available on Android and iOS.

properties.name: lensFacing
properties.docs: Configure the camera (front or back) to use.

properties.name: resolution
properties.docs:
Configure the resolution of the captured image that is used for barcode scanning.

If the resolution is not supported by the device, the closest supported resolution will be used.

Only available on Android and iOS.

properties.name: videoElement
properties.docs:
The HTML video element to use for the camera preview.

Only available on web.

properties.name: bytes
properties.docs: Raw bytes as it was encoded in the barcode.

properties.name: cornerPoints

tags.text: This property is experimental and may change in the future.
tags.name: experimental

properties.docs:
The four corner points of the barcode in clockwise
order starting with top-left.

This property is currently only supported by the `startScan(...)` method.

properties.name: displayValue
properties.docs: The barcode value in a human readable format.

properties.name: rawValue
properties.docs:
The barcode value in a machine readable format.

This value is only available when the barcode is encoded
in the UTF-8 character set. Otherwise, the `bytes` property
should be used and this property will be an empty string.

properties.name: urlBookmark
properties.docs: A URL and title from a 'MEBKM:'.

properties.name: wifi
properties.docs: A wifi network parameters from a 'WIFI:'.

properties.name: end
properties.docs: The event end date as ISO 8601 string.

properties.name: start
properties.docs: The event start date as ISO 8601 string.

properties.name: addressLines
properties.docs: Formatted address, multiple lines when appropriate.

properties.name: pronunciation
properties.docs: Text string to be set as the kana name in the phonebook. Used for Japanese contacts.

properties.name: documentType
properties.docs: "DL" for driver's licenses, "ID" for ID cards.

properties.name: issuingCountry
properties.docs: ISO 3166-1 alpha-3 code in which DL/ID was issued.

properties.name: phoneNumber
properties.docs: The phone number of the sms.

properties.name: message
properties.docs: The message content of the sms.

properties.name: path
